      "options": {
        "content": "## About This Dashboard\n\n**Project Alexandria** is a collaboratively maintained MCP knowledge base of tooling setup guides. The MCP server runs via **stdio** — it has no HTTP port and cannot be probed by Prometheus directly.\n\nThe **GitHub Pages docs site** is the only publicly reachable surface of this project and acts as a health proxy for GitHub Pages infrastructure.\n\n| Signal | Target |\n|---|---|\n| Uptime (UP / DOWN) | 7ports.github.io/project-alexandria |\n| Response time | 7ports.github.io/project-alexandria |\n| HTTP status code | 7ports.github.io/project-alexandria |\n\nIf Alexandria gains an HTTP API in future, re-run the Helldiver pipeline to add additional probes.\n\n*Onboarded by Helldiver Squadron Beta*",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "About Project Alexandria Monitoring",
      "type": "text"
    }
